snippet.textDisplay: I suppose the issue arises from the question of did Nintendo selling Rare cause them to lose value, or did Rare lose it's value before Nintendo sold them off and Nintendo just saw it coming? The last console game they released before the sale was Star Fox Adventures, and while that game was GARBAGE (opinion), I don't see how Nintendo would come to the conclusion that Rare is a sinking ship from just one game, especially when they brought over ten games that sold wonderfully on the N64 and SNES.

Just to call you up on a couple of things (not to embarrass you, just to let you know).

Firstly, Nintendo never 'had' Square. Square were third party, they just developed for Nintendo, rather than Sega. Which made perfect sense because Sega had their own RPG in Phantasy Star.
